{"title_page": "Jacques Bossis", "text_new": "{{short description|French cyclist}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name        = Jacques Bossis\n| image       = \n| full_name   = Jacques Bossis\n| nickname    = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1952|12|22|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Jonzac]], [[France]]\n| height      = \n| weight      = \n| currentteam = \n| discipline  = Road\n| role        = Rider\n| ridertype   = \n| proyears1   = \n| proteam1    = \n| majorwins   = GP Ouest-France (2x)\n}}\n\n'''Jacques Bossis''' (born 22 December 1952) is a French former professional [[Road bicycle racing|road bicycle racer]]. As an amateur he won Bordeaux-Saintes in 1973. He was professional from 1976 to 1985 and won 7 victories. He wore the yellow jersey as leader of the [[general classification in the Tour de France|general classification]] for one day in the [[1978 Tour de France]]. His victories include 1976 and 1977 editions of the [[GP Ouest-France]], 1981 [[Tour du Haut-Var]]. Since 1988 in the commune of Saujon in [[Charente-Maritime]] in [[France]], a cycling event called the ''la Jacques Bossis'' is organized which counts for the national amateur competition. He also competed in the [[Cycling at the 1972 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team pursuit|team pursuit]] event at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/bo/jacques-bossis-1.html |title=Jacques Bossis Olympic Results |accessdate=30 October 2014 |work=sports-reference.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141021043958/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/bo/jacques-bossis-1.html |archivedate=21 October 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1973\n:Bordeaux-Saintes\n;1976\n:[[GP Ouest-France]]\n;1977\n:[[GP Ouest-France]]\n;1978\n:Circuit de l'Indre\n:[[Cholet-Pays de Loire]]\n:{{FRA}} national track pursuit championships\n:[[Intermediate sprints classification in the Tour de France]]\n;1980\n:[[Grand Prix de Fourmies]]\n:Nogent-sur-Oise\n;1981\n:Planco\u00ebt\n:GP de Peymeinade\n:[[Tour du Haut Var]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Cycling Archives|2494}}\n*{{Tour de France results|4334|archive=20080416232148}}\n\n{{Maillot rouge}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bossis, Jacques}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Charente-Maritime]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of France]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1972 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:French track cyclists]]\n\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1950s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name        = Jacques Bossis\n| image       = \n| full_name   = Jacques Bossis\n| nickname    = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1952|12|22|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Jonzac]], [[France]]\n| height      = \n| weight      = \n| currentteam = \n| discipline  = Road\n| role        = Rider\n| ridertype   = \n| proyears1   = \n| proteam1    = \n| majorwins   = GP Ouest-France (2x)\n}}\n\n'''Jacques Bossis''' (born 22 December 1952) is a French former professional [[Road bicycle racing|road bicycle racer]]. As an amateur he won Bordeaux-Saintes in 1973. He was professional from 1976 to 1985 and won 7 victories. He wore the yellow jersey as leader of the [[general classification in the Tour de France|general classification]] for one day in the [[1978 Tour de France]]. His victories include 1976 and 1977 editions of the [[GP Ouest-France]], 1981 [[Tour du Haut-Var]]. Since 1988 in the commune of Saujon in [[Charente-Maritime]] in [[France]], a cycling event called the ''la Jacques Bossis'' is organized which counts for the national amateur competition. He also competed in the [[Cycling at the 1972 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's team pursuit|team pursuit]] event at the [[1972 Summer Olympics]].<ref name=\"sports-reference\">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/bo/jacques-bossis-1.html |title=Jacques Bossis Olympic Results |accessdate=30 October 2014 |work=sports-reference.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141021043958/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/bo/jacques-bossis-1.html |archivedate=21 October 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n;1973\n:Bordeaux-Saintes\n;1976\n:[[GP Ouest-France]]\n;1977\n:[[GP Ouest-France]]\n;1978\n:Circuit de l'Indre\n:[[Cholet-Pays de Loire]]\n:{{FRA}} national track pursuit championships\n:[[Intermediate sprints classification in the Tour de France]]\n;1980\n:[[Grand Prix de Fourmies]]\n:Nogent-sur-Oise\n;1981\n:Planco\u00ebt\n:GP de Peymeinade\n:[[Tour du Haut Var]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Cycling Archives|2494}}\n*{{Tour de France results|4334|archive=20080416232148}}\n\n{{Maillot rouge}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bossis, Jacques}}\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:French male cyclists]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Charente-Maritime]]\n[[Category:Tour de France cyclists]]\n[[Category:Olympic cyclists of France]]\n[[Category:Cyclists at the 1972 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:French track cyclists]]\n\n\n{{France-cycling-bio-1950s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:added short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jacques_Bossis"}
